1
00:01:25,381 --> 00:01:26,347
- UNH.

2
00:01:26,381 --> 00:01:29,463
I'M HOME, GRANDPA!
MIND RUNNING A BATH FOR ME?

3
00:01:29,463 --> 00:01:30,429
I'D BETTER HURRY,

4
00:01:30,463 --> 00:01:31,563
OR I'LL BE LATE
FOR SCHOOL AGAIN.

5
00:01:31,596 --> 00:01:34,196
- SHINGLES? IS THAT SERIOUS?
- THAT SOUNDS LIKE HOJO.

6
00:01:34,229 --> 00:01:38,696
- IT'S A NASTY FORM OF HERPES,
UH, FROM A CHICKEN POX VIRUS.

7
00:01:38,729 --> 00:01:42,296
- THAT DOES SOUND NASTY.
LAST WEEK, SHE HAD RHEUMATISM.

8
00:01:42,329 --> 00:01:43,429
HERE, THIS MIGHT HELP.

9
00:01:43,463 --> 00:01:46,596
- OH, YOUR MOM'S GOING TO GO
BROKE GIVING ALL THIS AWAY.

10
00:01:46,629 --> 00:01:47,496
THANK YOU.

11
00:01:47,529 --> 00:01:49,096
I'LL THINK OF YOU
WHEN I PUT THIS ON MY--

12
00:01:49,129 --> 00:01:51,596
I MEAN,
KAGOME'S SWOLLEN ANKLES.

13
00:01:51,629 --> 00:01:52,729
- IT IS HOJO!

14
00:01:52,763 --> 00:01:56,229
AND GRAMPS IS TELLING HIM
ANOTHER BOGUS STORY!

15
00:01:56,629 --> 00:01:58,896
- HEE HEE HEE!

16
00:01:58,929 --> 00:02:00,096
- SO, HOW'S MY RHEUMATISM?

17
00:02:00,129 --> 00:02:01,963
- KAGOME, YOU SHOULDN'T BE
OUT HERE IN YOUR CONDITION!

18
00:02:01,996 --> 00:02:04,863
NOW, GET BACK INTO BED AND PUT
YOUR FEET UP ON SOME PILLOWS

19
00:02:04,896 --> 00:02:06,629
BEFORE THE SWELLING
GETS TOO BAD!

20
00:02:06,663 --> 00:02:07,629
- I DON'T HAVE ANY SWELLING!

21
00:02:07,663 --> 00:02:09,163
AND IF YOU'D QUIT TELLING
ALL THESE STORIES,

22
00:02:09,196 --> 00:02:10,596
I MIGHT BE ABLE TO GO TO SCHOOL
FOR A CHANGE!

23
00:02:10,629 --> 00:02:12,596
- WELL, SOMEBODY GOT UP ON
THE WRONG SIDE OF THE BED!

24
00:02:12,629 --> 00:02:15,296
- NOBODY EXCEPT MY FAMILY
KNOWS OF MY EXCURSIONS

25
00:02:15,329 --> 00:02:18,296
THROUGH THE HIDDEN WELL
INTO THE FEUDAL ERA.

26
00:02:18,329 --> 00:02:19,863
EVEN IF I TOLD
SOME OF MY FRIENDS,

27
00:02:19,896 --> 00:02:22,329
I DOUBT THAT ANYONE WOULD
BELIEVE ME.

28
00:02:22,363 --> 00:02:25,496
CAN YOU BLAME ME
FOR KEEPING IT TO MYSELF?

29
00:02:34,563 --> 00:02:37,296
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

30
00:02:39,463 --> 00:02:42,529
- THERE YOU GO.

31
00:02:42,563 --> 00:02:43,463
- [SIGHS]

32
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:44,996
- KAGOME,
I HEAR YOU HAVE TO TAKE

33
00:02:45,029 --> 00:02:47,096
THE MAKE-UP COURSE
FOR MATH, TOO.

34
00:02:47,129 --> 00:02:50,129
- YEAH, I FOUND OUT LAST WEEK.

35
00:02:50,163 --> 00:02:50,996
- I DON'T GET IT.

36
00:02:51,029 --> 00:02:52,263
YOU'VE ALWAYS HAD
TOP MARKS

37
00:02:52,296 --> 00:02:53,896
IN THE MATH CLASS
UP UNTIL NOW.

38
00:02:53,929 --> 00:02:55,763
WONDER IF HOJO
WILL KEEP COMING AROUND

39
00:02:55,796 --> 00:02:57,029
IF HE FINDS OUT
ABOUT YOUR GRADES?

40
00:02:57,063 --> 00:02:59,729
- SO, WHAT DID YOUR NEW
BOYFRIEND BRING YOU THIS TIME?

41
00:02:59,763 --> 00:03:00,796
MAYBE SOME ARTHRITIS CREAM?

42
00:03:00,829 --> 00:03:03,296
- HE'S NOT MY BOYFRIEND!
AND IT WASN'T FOR ARTHRITIS!

43
00:03:03,329 --> 00:03:05,563
THEY WERE EXPENSIVE PLASTERS
TO TREAT MY RHEUMATISM!

44
00:03:05,596 --> 00:03:08,663
- BUT I THOUGHT RHEUMATISM WAS
A KIND OF ARTHRITIS.

45
00:03:08,696 --> 00:03:09,696
- UH...UH, YEAH.

46
00:03:09,729 --> 00:03:11,429
I'M SO CAUGHT UP
IN GRANDPA'S TALES,

47
00:03:11,463 --> 00:03:12,363
I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S WHAT!

48
00:03:12,396 --> 00:03:14,096
HOW AM I EVER GONNA MAKE IT
INTO HIGH SCHOOL

49
00:03:14,129 --> 00:03:15,463
WITH ALL THESE CLASSES I MISS?

50
00:03:15,496 --> 00:03:18,563
- HEY, LOOK!
THEY'VE GOT FIREWORKS!

51
00:03:18,596 --> 00:03:19,663
- HA! COOL!

52
00:03:19,696 --> 00:03:22,463
- REMEMBER WHEN WE USED TO DO
THAT WHEN WE WERE KIDS?

53
00:03:24,529 --> 00:03:26,996
- HUH?

54
00:03:35,929 --> 00:03:37,196
- OH, MY GOD!
- OH, NO!

55
00:03:37,229 --> 00:03:39,296
- JOHNNY, COME BACK HERE!
- GET AWAY FROM THAT!

56
00:03:39,329 --> 00:03:40,629
DON'T TOUCH ANYTHING!
BE CAREFUL!

57
00:03:40,663 --> 00:03:43,163
- HEH HEH HEH!
THAT'LL KEEP THEM BUSY!

58
00:03:43,196 --> 00:03:45,196
LITTLE BRATS!

59
00:03:45,229 --> 00:03:47,863
- NO! STOP! HEY!

60
00:03:48,496 --> 00:03:51,196
HOLD IT RIGHT THERE!

61
00:03:53,129 --> 00:03:55,096
WHAT'D YOU SCARE
ALL THOSE KIDS FOR?

62
00:03:55,129 --> 00:03:56,229
THAT WASN'T VERY NICE!

63
00:03:56,263 --> 00:03:58,263
- WAIT A SECOND.
YOU MEAN YOU CAN SEE ME?

64
00:03:58,296 --> 00:04:03,029
- WHAT'S WITH THIS GIRL?
SHE DOESN'T EVEN HAVE
ANY SHOES ON.

65
00:04:04,763 --> 00:04:09,163
AND WHY IS SHE WEARING A DOWN
JACKET WHEN IT'S ALMOST SUMMER?

66
00:04:09,196 --> 00:04:11,596
LOOK, YOU OWE THOSE KIDS
AN APOLOGY.

67
00:04:11,629 --> 00:04:13,529
I'LL COME WITH YOU
TO MAKE IT EASIER.

68
00:04:13,563 --> 00:04:15,096
- MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS!

69
00:04:15,129 --> 00:04:16,963
UNH!
- AAH!

70
00:04:16,996 --> 00:04:17,796
OH! UNH!

71
00:04:17,829 --> 00:04:19,829
- I DON'T WANT TO TALK
TO YOU ANYMORE!

72
00:04:19,863 --> 00:04:22,496
LEAVE ME ALONE!

73
00:04:23,163 --> 00:04:25,629
- OH!

74
00:04:29,563 --> 00:04:30,929
[SIGHS]

75
00:04:30,963 --> 00:04:32,596
- WHAT'D YOU RUN OFF FOR,
KAGOME?

76
00:04:32,629 --> 00:04:34,863
- HOW COME YOU WERE
TALKING TO YOURSELF?

77
00:04:34,896 --> 00:04:36,663
- UH...

78
00:04:36,696 --> 00:04:38,829
SHE VANISHED!
AM I LOSING IT?

79
00:04:38,863 --> 00:04:42,329
NO, THAT GIRL WAS REAL.
I FELT HER HAND!

80
00:04:42,363 --> 00:04:44,896
[BUZZING]

81
00:04:47,996 --> 00:04:51,529
- HOW MUCH LONGER
IS THIS GONNA TAKE, ANYWAY?

82
00:04:51,563 --> 00:04:52,729
- AHH, BE PATIENT, MY LORD.

83
00:04:52,763 --> 00:04:56,296
IF YOU TRY TO TAKE THE SHEATH
FROM THE STEEL WASPS NOW,

84
00:04:56,329 --> 00:04:57,296
YOU'LL BE STUNG TO DEATH.

85
00:04:57,329 --> 00:05:00,229
THE SHEATH OF YOUR SWORD
WAS BADLY CRACKED

86
00:05:00,263 --> 00:05:01,363
DURING YOUR LAST BATTLE.

87
00:05:01,396 --> 00:05:03,229
LET THE STEEL WASPS
DO THEIR JOB

88
00:05:03,263 --> 00:05:05,963
AND REPAIR IT
WITH THEIR SPECIAL WAX.

89
00:05:05,996 --> 00:05:08,763
- WOO!
HEY, HOW ABOUT A BITE?

90
00:05:08,796 --> 00:05:09,629
AHH!

91
00:05:09,663 --> 00:05:12,229
- [GRUNTING]

92
00:05:13,696 --> 00:05:16,296
HEY! I WAS ONLY TRYING TO LIVEN
THINGS UP AROUND HERE!

93
00:05:16,329 --> 00:05:20,896
WHERE'S KAGOME, ANYWAYS?
I'M GETTING TIRED OF
HANGING AROUND WITH YOU.

94
00:05:20,929 --> 00:05:22,363
- FUNNY YOU SHOULD
MENTION THAT.

95
00:05:22,396 --> 00:05:26,696
- IT'S NOT FAIR!
WHY DO I HAVE TO BE
ALONE WITH YOU?

96
00:05:26,729 --> 00:05:27,596
- HUH!

97
00:05:27,629 --> 00:05:30,696
- UM, DON'T I DESERVE
TO BE COUNTED, HMM?

98
00:05:30,729 --> 00:05:33,696
- [GIGGLING]

99
00:05:33,729 --> 00:05:35,696
- WHAT'S THAT?
- IT'S A DEMON!

100
00:05:35,729 --> 00:05:38,529
- WHY ARE YOU SCARED?
YOU'RE A DEMON, TOO, REMEMBER?

101
00:05:38,563 --> 00:05:41,329
- THAT'S NO ORDINARY DEMON.
IT'S THE SOUL PIPER.

102
00:05:41,363 --> 00:05:45,763
WHEN A CHILD DIES,
THE SOUL PIPER STAYS
AND PLAYS WITH THAT CHILD

103
00:05:45,796 --> 00:05:48,196
UNTIL THE SOUL IS READY
TO REST IN PEACE.

104
00:05:48,229 --> 00:05:51,563
AS LONG AS THE EYES
OF THE MONSTER REMAIN CLOSED,

105
00:05:51,596 --> 00:05:53,163
THERE'S NOTHING
TO BE AFRAID OF.

106
00:05:53,196 --> 00:05:55,963
BUT WHEN THE SOUL PIPER'S
EYES OPEN,

107
00:05:55,996 --> 00:05:58,829
IT BECOMES A FEARFUL DEMON.

108
00:05:58,863 --> 00:06:01,429
- [GIGGLING]

109
00:06:01,929 --> 00:06:05,296
- COME ON, MOM!
IT'S SATURDAY!

110
00:06:06,596 --> 00:06:09,963
WHY DO I HAVE TO TAKE YOU TO SEE
YOUR FRIEND IN THE HOSPITAL?

111
00:06:09,996 --> 00:06:12,263
IT'S NOT FAIR.

112
00:06:12,296 --> 00:06:13,296
- I CAN'T HELP IT.

113
00:06:13,329 --> 00:06:15,596
MOM'S BUSY, AND I'M NOT
ALLOWED TO TAKE THE TRAIN

114
00:06:15,629 --> 00:06:17,396
BY MYSELF, REMEMBER?

115
00:06:17,429 --> 00:06:18,296
- YEAH, YEAH.

116
00:06:18,329 --> 00:06:21,329
BUT I DON'T WANT TO STAY THERE
ALL DAY, OK?

117
00:06:21,996 --> 00:06:24,296
- UH, HEY, SIS?
- UH-HUH?

118
00:06:24,329 --> 00:06:28,429
- DO YOU THINK EVIL GHOSTS
REALLY EXIST?

119
00:06:28,463 --> 00:06:30,196
- HUH?

120
00:06:30,229 --> 00:06:32,896
- OH, SOTA!
IT'S SO NICE OF YOU TO VISIT.

121
00:06:32,929 --> 00:06:35,763
- HOW'S SATORU?
WILL HE BE GETTING OUT SOON?

122
00:06:35,796 --> 00:06:38,029
- I'M AFRAID HE'LL BE IN HERE
FOR A WHILE YET.

123
00:06:38,063 --> 00:06:40,429
HE STILL HASN'T WOKEN UP
SINCE THE ACCIDENT.

124
00:06:40,463 --> 00:06:42,096
- WELL, MAYBE THESE
WILL HELP.

125
00:06:42,129 --> 00:06:46,329
- GET-WELL CRANES.
HOW VERY THOUGHTFUL
OF YOU, SOTA.

126
00:06:46,363 --> 00:06:49,863
- HER HANDS ARE BURNED.
- HMM? OH, THESE.

127
00:06:49,896 --> 00:06:52,363
THEY WERE BURNED IN THE FIRE.

128
00:06:52,396 --> 00:06:53,729
- I DIDN'T MEAN TO STARE!

129
00:06:53,763 --> 00:06:55,829
- FORTUNATELY,
HE WASN'T BURNED,

130
00:06:55,863 --> 00:06:58,096
BUT HE'S BEEN IN A COMA
FOR HALF A YEAR--

131
00:06:58,129 --> 00:07:00,763
SINCE THE FIRE.

132
00:07:06,263 --> 00:07:08,529
- AAH!
- AAH!

133
00:07:08,563 --> 00:07:10,729
OH!
HUH?

134
00:07:10,763 --> 00:07:13,829
THAT'S THE SAME GIRL I SAW
IN THE PARK!

135
00:07:14,063 --> 00:07:16,529
WHAT'S GOING ON?
- NOT AGAIN!

136
00:07:16,563 --> 00:07:18,729
- HUH?
- WHY DOES THIS KEEP HAPPENING?

137
00:07:18,763 --> 00:07:22,129
- WHO IS THAT GIRL?
WHAT DOES SHE WANT?

138
00:07:22,163 --> 00:07:25,729
I'VE GOT TO GET
TO THE BOTTOM OF THIS!

139
00:07:28,596 --> 00:07:31,063
[FLUTE PLAYING]

140
00:07:31,096 --> 00:07:32,163
- ONE OF THESE DAYS,

141
00:07:32,196 --> 00:07:36,329
I'M GONNA FINISH OFF
MY STUPID BROTHER FOR GOOD!

142
00:07:36,696 --> 00:07:39,063
- WHY WERE YOU ASKING
ABOUT EVIL GHOSTS

143
00:07:39,096 --> 00:07:40,429
BEFORE WE GOT
TO THE HOSPITAL?

144
00:07:40,463 --> 00:07:44,363
- SOME PEOPLE IN OUR CLASS
THINK THERE'S AN EVIL GHOST
AFTER SATORU.

145
00:07:44,396 --> 00:07:47,396
HE'S BEEN IN A COMA
FOR 6 MONTHS NOW, RIGHT?

146
00:07:47,429 --> 00:07:49,563
EVERYONE FROM THE CLASS
USED TO COME

147
00:07:49,596 --> 00:07:50,629
AND VISIT HIM
ALL THE TIME,

148
00:07:50,663 --> 00:07:53,663
BUT THEN ALL KINDS OF
WEIRD THINGS STARTED HAPPENING

149
00:07:53,696 --> 00:07:54,996
WHEN THEY CAME TO SEE HIM.

150
00:07:55,029 --> 00:07:57,496
LIKE, THEY WERE
PUSHED DOWN STAIRS,

151
00:07:57,529 --> 00:08:00,129
ALMOST HIT BY CARS,
AND OTHER STUFF.

152
00:08:00,163 --> 00:08:02,363
EVERYONE'S SCARED
TO VISIT HIM NOW.

153
00:08:02,396 --> 00:08:05,529
HIS SISTER MAYU DIED
IN THE FIRE, YOU KNOW?

154
00:08:05,563 --> 00:08:06,963
SOME GUYS
IN THE CLASS THINK

155
00:08:06,996 --> 00:08:10,663
MAYBE SHE'S DOING
ALL THE CREEPY STUFF.

156
00:08:14,363 --> 00:08:16,329
- AND THAT'S
WHERE THEIR APARTMENT WAS?

157
00:08:16,363 --> 00:08:17,696
- YEAH. THEY KEPT TRYING
TO CLEAN IT UP

158
00:08:17,729 --> 00:08:21,963
AND REBUILD IT AFTER THE FIRE,
BUT EVERY TIME SOMEONE GOT NEAR,

159
00:08:21,996 --> 00:08:24,863
THERE WAS ANOTHER ACCIDENT.

160
00:08:26,596 --> 00:08:28,063
- LOOK OUT!
- AAH!

161
00:08:28,096 --> 00:08:30,029
- AAH!
- UNH!

162
00:08:30,063 --> 00:08:33,296
SEE? I TOLD YOU THERE WAS
AN EVIL GHOST AROUND!

163
00:08:33,329 --> 00:08:35,596
AAH! OOH!
- SOTA!

164
00:08:35,629 --> 00:08:37,496
HELP!
HUH?

165
00:08:37,529 --> 00:08:40,263
NO! GET OFF OF THERE!

166
00:08:41,363 --> 00:08:43,796
OH!

167
00:08:44,029 --> 00:08:46,029
HUH?
- DUH! I'M DEAD!

168
00:08:46,063 --> 00:08:48,496
DON'T YOU GET IT?

169
00:08:48,529 --> 00:08:50,396
- YOU'RE MAYU,
SATORU'S SISTER!

170
00:08:50,429 --> 00:08:51,629
WHY ARE YOU BEING SO MEAN?

171
00:08:51,663 --> 00:08:55,096
YOU DON'T REALLY WANT
TO HURT PEOPLE, DO YOU?

172
00:08:55,129 --> 00:08:56,763
- I DON'T CARE ABOUT ANYONE,

173
00:08:56,796 --> 00:08:59,763
ESPECIALLY NOT MY MOMMY.

174
00:08:59,796 --> 00:09:01,496
MOMMY COULDN'T STAND ME.

175
00:09:01,529 --> 00:09:03,496
SHE DIDN'T EVEN CARE
THAT I DIED!

176
00:09:03,529 --> 00:09:05,296
SHE LEFT ME IN THE FIRE.

177
00:09:05,329 --> 00:09:07,129
SHE ONLY SAVED
MY LITTLE BROTHER.

178
00:09:07,163 --> 00:09:09,163
- I'M SURE
YOU'RE WRONG ABOUT THAT.

179
00:09:09,196 --> 00:09:10,496
I'VE TALKED TO
YOUR MOTHER, MAYU.

180
00:09:10,529 --> 00:09:12,996
I'M SURE SHE LOVED YOU
AS MUCH AS YOUR BROTHER.

181
00:09:13,029 --> 00:09:14,229
- WHAT DO YOU KNOW?!

182
00:09:14,263 --> 00:09:18,363
YOU'D BETTER STAY OUT OF MY WAY,
OR I'LL HAVE TO KILL YOU, TOO!

183
00:09:18,396 --> 00:09:20,696
- OH!

184
00:09:20,729 --> 00:09:23,163
AAH!

185
00:09:32,263 --> 00:09:33,929
UNH...

186
00:09:33,963 --> 00:09:34,763
HUH?

187
00:09:34,796 --> 00:09:36,996
- [WHISTLING]

188
00:09:37,029 --> 00:09:39,496
- HUH?

189
00:09:42,263 --> 00:09:44,963
WHAT IS THAT THING?

190
00:09:46,296 --> 00:09:49,129
"WHEN THE EYES OPEN WIDE..."

191
00:09:51,396 --> 00:09:52,763
IT'S GONE!

192
00:09:52,796 --> 00:09:55,263
WHAT WAS IT TRYING TO
TELL ME?

193
00:09:55,296 --> 00:09:57,696
YOU'VE HEARD OF IT, THEN?

194
00:09:57,729 --> 00:09:59,963
SO THAT DEMON IS KNOWN AS
THE SOUL PIPER?

195
00:09:59,996 --> 00:10:03,063
- YES. IT SOUNDS LIKE WE'RE
TALKING ABOUT THE SAME THING.

196
00:10:03,096 --> 00:10:05,263
THE SOUL PIPER CONSOLES
THE CHILDREN

197
00:10:05,296 --> 00:10:06,829
UNTIL THEY CAN ACCEPT
THEIR DEATHS.

198
00:10:06,863 --> 00:10:09,663
IT ENTERTAINS THE CHILDREN
WITH ITS FLUTE

199
00:10:09,696 --> 00:10:11,696
UNTIL THEY CAN FIND PEACE.

200
00:10:11,729 --> 00:10:12,929
- WOW!
- AHH!

201
00:10:12,963 --> 00:10:14,529
- WHAT IF THEY CAN'T FIND PEACE?

202
00:10:14,563 --> 00:10:16,896
WHAT IF THEY HAVE SOMETHING
HOLDING THEM BACK,

203
00:10:16,929 --> 00:10:18,296
LIKE JEALOUSY OR HATRED?

204
00:10:18,329 --> 00:10:20,529
- THEN THE CHILDREN BECOME
EVIL SPIRITS.

205
00:10:20,563 --> 00:10:21,663
- YOU'RE NOT SERIOUS!

206
00:10:21,696 --> 00:10:24,496
- YOU'VE HEARD OF POLTERGEISTS,
FULL OF RAGE AND HATRED.

207
00:10:24,529 --> 00:10:27,596
WHEN THE SOUL PIPER SENSES
THE CHILD'S RAGE, ITS EYES OPEN,

208
00:10:27,629 --> 00:10:31,096
AND THE SOUL PIPER HURLS
THE CHILD INTO THE DEPTHS
OF HELL.

209
00:10:31,129 --> 00:10:34,763
- MOST OF THE TIME,
THE SOUL PIPER'S EYES
ARE CLOSED,

210
00:10:34,796 --> 00:10:37,329
BUT LOOK OUT
WHEN THEY OPEN!

211
00:10:37,363 --> 00:10:38,363
- THEY WERE OPENING!

212
00:10:38,396 --> 00:10:40,663
I'VE GOT TO DO SOMETHING
TO SAVE MAYU!

213
00:10:40,696 --> 00:10:42,929
- LET IT BE, KAGOME.
- HUH?

214
00:10:42,963 --> 00:10:45,363
- GHOSTS AND SPIRITS
AREN'T LIKE MONSTERS.

215
00:10:45,396 --> 00:10:47,129
WE CAN'T JUST TAKE OUT
OUR SWORDS

216
00:10:47,163 --> 00:10:48,263
AND START ORDERING THEM AROUND.

217
00:10:48,296 --> 00:10:51,129
GHOSTS ARE DIFFERENT
AND MUCH MORE DANGEROUS.

218
00:10:51,163 --> 00:10:52,463
- I DON'T CARE IF THEY ARE!

219
00:10:52,496 --> 00:10:54,429
I COME FROM A LONG LINE
OF PRIESTS.

220
00:10:54,463 --> 00:10:56,363
I WON'T SIT BY
AND WATCH SOMEONE SUFFER!

221
00:10:56,396 --> 00:10:58,429
- HEH!
WELL, YOU CAN COUNT ME OUT.

222
00:10:58,463 --> 00:11:01,696
THERE'S NOTHING YOU CAN DO
TO HELP THE GIRL AT THIS POINT.

223
00:11:01,729 --> 00:11:02,463
HUH?

224
00:11:02,496 --> 00:11:03,896
- YOU SHOULDN'T
TALK TO YOURSELF.

225
00:11:03,929 --> 00:11:05,963
PEOPLE WILL WONDER.

226
00:11:05,996 --> 00:11:06,763
- GRR!

227
00:11:06,796 --> 00:11:08,463
- I CAN'T LET HER CARRY ON
LIKE THIS!

228
00:11:08,496 --> 00:11:12,863
POOR MAYU!
SHE'S ALREADY SUFFERED SO MUCH!

229
00:11:22,063 --> 00:11:26,063
- MOMMY, I CAN'T WAIT TO TRY ON
MY NEW KIMONO!

230
00:11:26,096 --> 00:11:27,329
I'LL WEAR IT TO THE FESTIVAL

231
00:11:27,363 --> 00:11:30,629
AND CATCH LOTS OF GOLDFISH
FRIENDS FOR MY NEW TANK!

232
00:11:30,663 --> 00:11:32,063
ARE YOU ALMOST FINISHED,
MOM?

233
00:11:32,096 --> 00:11:35,196
- ALMOST.
BUT THE FESTIVAL'S
STILL A LONG WAY OFF.

234
00:11:35,229 --> 00:11:37,463
- YEAH, I KNOW,
BUT I WANT TO TRY IT!

235
00:11:37,496 --> 00:11:40,629
- YES, HONEY.
HEE HEE HEE!

236
00:11:46,429 --> 00:11:49,063
- THIS TIME,
WHEN MOM LEAVES THE HOSPITAL,

237
00:11:49,096 --> 00:11:52,429
I'M GONNA MAKE SURE THAT SATORU
HAS AN ACCIDENT.

238
00:11:52,463 --> 00:11:55,129
- [FLUTE PLAYING]

239
00:12:03,163 --> 00:12:04,096
- HUH?
- WHAT'S SHE DOING?

240
00:12:04,129 --> 00:12:06,496
- SURE, THANK YOU.
OH, GOOD NIGHT, MRS. AKAIDA.

241
00:12:06,529 --> 00:12:09,096
SEE YOU TOMORROW.
WE'LL CALL IF THERE'S ANY NEWS.

242
00:12:09,129 --> 00:12:11,296
- THANKS.
GOOD NIGHT.

243
00:12:11,329 --> 00:12:12,896
- HAVE A GOOD NIGHT'S REST.

244
00:12:12,929 --> 00:12:14,596
- MRS. AKAIDA!
- HELLO!

245
00:12:14,629 --> 00:12:17,663
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
VISITING HOURS ARE OVER, DEAR.

246
00:12:17,696 --> 00:12:20,229
- I KNOW, BUT I NEED
TO TALK TO YOU.

247
00:12:20,263 --> 00:12:21,563
IT'S ABOUT MAYU!

248
00:12:21,596 --> 00:12:24,296
[SIREN IN DISTANCE]

249
00:12:26,063 --> 00:12:29,196
- AROUND THE BACK.
WE'RE ALL READY FOR YOU!

250
00:12:33,229 --> 00:12:36,129
- IT SEEMS LIKE JUST YESTERDAY.

251
00:12:38,996 --> 00:12:39,929
- I HATE YOU, MOMMY!

252
00:12:39,963 --> 00:12:41,329
WHY DIDN'T YOU COME TO
THE SCHOOL'S OPEN HOUSE?

253
00:12:41,363 --> 00:12:45,796
- I'M SORRY, MAYU,
BUT YOUR BROTHER'S BEEN
SICK IN BED ALL DAY.

254
00:12:45,829 --> 00:12:47,796
- IT'S ALWAYS ABOUT
STUPID SATORU!

255
00:12:47,829 --> 00:12:51,229
- HUH? THAT'S NOT TRUE!
- I CAN'T STAND YOU OR SATORU!

256
00:12:51,263 --> 00:12:55,096
- MAYU!
DON'T RUN OUT ON ME!

257
00:12:55,129 --> 00:12:57,063
[DOOR SHUTS]

258
00:12:57,096 --> 00:13:01,296
IT SEEMED WE WERE ALWAYS HAVING
ARGUMENTS LIKE THAT.

259
00:13:01,329 --> 00:13:02,496
I THOUGHT
I HEARD THE DOOR SLAM,

260
00:13:02,529 --> 00:13:05,229
AND I ASSUMED THAT SHE'D RUN OFF
TO THE NEIGHBORS' APARTMENT,

261
00:13:05,263 --> 00:13:07,196
AS SHE USUALLY DID.

262
00:13:07,229 --> 00:13:09,863
I WAS MISTAKEN.

263
00:13:13,929 --> 00:13:16,463
[NO AUDIO]

264
00:13:37,596 --> 00:13:41,496
HOW COULD I HAVE KNOWN THAT MAYU
WAS STILL INSIDE?

265
00:13:46,529 --> 00:13:49,596
- WE GOT A BODY IN HERE!
POOR THING.

266
00:13:49,629 --> 00:13:51,129
LOOKS LIKE JUST A KID.

267
00:13:51,163 --> 00:13:53,596
- IF I HAD KNOWN,
I WOULD HAVE GONE BACK IN.

268
00:13:53,629 --> 00:13:56,063
BUT I WAS SO SURE
THAT SHE WASN'T THERE!

269
00:13:56,096 --> 00:13:57,763
- SO MAYU'S MOM DIDN'T
EVEN KNOW

270
00:13:57,796 --> 00:14:00,396
SHE WAS STILL IN THE APARTMENT
DURING THE FIRE!

271
00:14:00,429 --> 00:14:01,429
[GLASS SHATTERING]

272
00:14:01,463 --> 00:14:02,296
[BOTH GASP]

273
00:14:02,329 --> 00:14:05,363
- THAT'S SATORU'S ROOM!
- IT'S MAYU!

274
00:14:08,529 --> 00:14:10,929
MAYU, NO!
STOP DOING THIS!

275
00:14:10,963 --> 00:14:14,896
LET'S TALK!
THIS IS ALL A MISUNDERSTANDING!

276
00:14:15,429 --> 00:14:18,096
- OH! MAYU!
BUT YOU--

277
00:14:18,129 --> 00:14:20,496
- STAY OUT!
- AAH! UNH!

278
00:14:20,529 --> 00:14:21,429
UNH!

279
00:14:21,463 --> 00:14:23,996
- DON'T BLAME YOUR MOM!
TRY AND THINK BACK!

280
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:26,663
YOUR MOM DIDN'T
ABANDON YOU IN THE FIRE.

281
00:14:26,696 --> 00:14:28,696
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

282
00:14:28,729 --> 00:14:32,363
SHE DIDN'T THINK YOU WERE
AT HOME WHEN THE FIRE HAPPENED!

283
00:14:32,396 --> 00:14:34,929
REMEMBER?

284
00:14:36,163 --> 00:14:38,629
- OOH! IT'S NICE
AND WARM IN HERE.

285
00:14:38,663 --> 00:14:40,229
- OHH, HI THERE, MAYU.

286
00:14:40,263 --> 00:14:43,496
MOM SAID YOU'RE NOT
SUPPOSED TO HANG STUFF

287
00:14:43,529 --> 00:14:45,796
OVER THE STOVE WHEN IT'S ON,
REMEMBER?

288
00:14:45,829 --> 00:14:48,663
- YOU GOING TO SNITCH ON ME?

289
00:14:50,263 --> 00:14:52,029
I'M GONNA PLAY A TRICK ON MOMMY.

290
00:14:52,063 --> 00:14:54,663
DON'T TELL HER I'M IN HERE,
OR I'LL BE MAD!

291
00:14:54,696 --> 00:14:57,696
I'M GONNA MAKE HER
WORRY ABOUT ME!

292
00:14:57,729 --> 00:14:59,629
I LEFT MY SCARF
OVER THE STOVE.

293
00:14:59,663 --> 00:15:01,929
IT MUST HAVE FALLEN
AND CAUGHT FIRE!

294
00:15:01,963 --> 00:15:04,796
IT WAS MY FAULT
OUR APARTMENT BURNED DOWN.

295
00:15:04,829 --> 00:15:07,696
MOMMY DIDN'T KNOW I WAS HOME.

296
00:15:08,096 --> 00:15:10,196
- MAYU...
- I FORGOT THAT.

297
00:15:10,229 --> 00:15:15,196
BUT IT DOESN'T MATTER,
BECAUSE I STILL HATE HER!

298
00:15:15,229 --> 00:15:17,863
- AAH!
UGH...

299
00:15:18,396 --> 00:15:20,929
- SATORU!

300
00:15:22,729 --> 00:15:24,429
OH!

301
00:15:24,463 --> 00:15:25,929
THE POOR BOY!

302
00:15:25,963 --> 00:15:28,063
- CAN'T YOU HANDLE ANYTHING
ON YOUR OWN?

303
00:15:28,096 --> 00:15:30,629
- OH! HMM?

304
00:15:31,429 --> 00:15:33,229
INUYASHA!

305
00:15:33,263 --> 00:15:35,396
YOU CAME TO HELP ME!

306
00:15:35,429 --> 00:15:39,329
- GOOD THING I DID, TOO,
OR THIS KID WOULD BE IN TROUBLE.

307
00:15:39,363 --> 00:15:43,029
GIVE UP ON THE GIRL.
IT'S TOO LATE FOR HER.

308
00:15:43,563 --> 00:15:46,963
EVEN IF YOU DO MAKE HER REALIZE
WHAT HAPPENED AND MAKE HER STOP,

309
00:15:46,996 --> 00:15:50,729
I GUARANTEE YOU SHE'S NOT GOING
ANYWHERE NEAR HEAVEN.

310
00:15:52,096 --> 00:15:54,763
- LOOK! ITS EYES!

311
00:15:58,596 --> 00:16:01,096
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
LET ME GO!

312
00:16:01,129 --> 00:16:03,829
I WANT TO STAY HERE!

313
00:16:11,072 --> 00:16:12,272
- I'M MAKING THIS UP
AS I GO,

314
00:16:12,306 --> 00:16:14,872
BECAUSE LIKE I TOLD YOU,
I'M NO EXPERT IN SPIRITS
AND GHOSTS.

315
00:16:14,906 --> 00:16:19,706
- I KNOW, BUT WE'VE GOT TO DO
WHATEVER WE CAN TO STOP MAYU
FROM GOING TO HELL!

316
00:16:19,739 --> 00:16:21,406
- WE'VE GOT TO FIND
THE GIRL'S APARTMENT.

317
00:16:21,439 --> 00:16:23,439
ACCORDING TO MYOGA,
THE SOUL PIPER DRAGS

318
00:16:23,472 --> 00:16:25,372
THE TORMENTED SOUL
TO ITS PLACE OF DEATH,

319
00:16:25,406 --> 00:16:28,439
THEN HURLS IT
INTO THE PITS OF HELL.

320
00:16:33,539 --> 00:16:34,606
UNH!

321
00:16:34,639 --> 00:16:37,872
THAT MUST BE IT.
LET'S JUST HOPE
WE'RE NOT TOO LATE.

322
00:16:39,939 --> 00:16:43,206
UNH!
- THIS IS GOOD.
LET ME HANDLE IT FROM HERE.

323
00:16:43,239 --> 00:16:45,439
- LIKE YOU HANDLED THE KID
BACK AT THE HOSPITAL?

324
00:16:45,472 --> 00:16:47,906
I DON'T THINK SO.
I'M GOING WITH YOU.

325
00:16:47,939 --> 00:16:49,572
I CAN RELATE TO WHOEVER
FIRST SAID,

326
00:16:49,606 --> 00:16:53,039
"THERE'S NOTHING SCARIER
THAN AN IGNORAMUS."

327
00:16:53,706 --> 00:16:55,206
HUH?
SHE DISAPPEARED!

328
00:16:55,239 --> 00:16:58,139
RIGHT--THIS IS THE
DIMENSION WHERE HUMANS
ARE DRAGGED INTO HELL!

329
00:16:58,172 --> 00:17:01,306
I'M HALF-DEMON, SO I CAN'T
MAKE IT PAST THIS BARRIER!

330
00:17:01,339 --> 00:17:06,839
OH, DAMN. KAGOME CANNOT
HANDLE THIS ON HER OWN!

331
00:17:06,872 --> 00:17:11,572
- WHERE AM I?
WHY IS IT SO DARK IN HERE?

332
00:17:11,606 --> 00:17:12,672
[CHAINS RATTLING]

333
00:17:12,706 --> 00:17:14,506
THE LIGHT'S ON.

334
00:17:14,539 --> 00:17:15,539
HUH?

335
00:17:15,572 --> 00:17:18,139
[SCREAMING]

336
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:22,639
- HUH?
- YOU'RE AWAKE.

337
00:17:22,672 --> 00:17:24,372
HOW DO YOU FEEL?
- HUH?

338
00:17:24,406 --> 00:17:26,772
WHERE AM I?
WHAT HAPPENED?

339
00:17:26,806 --> 00:17:29,039
- SATORU HAS WOKEN UP.

340
00:17:29,072 --> 00:17:30,406
- HUH?

341
00:17:30,439 --> 00:17:32,939
SATORU!

342
00:17:33,439 --> 00:17:36,606
- UNH...
M-MOMMY?

343
00:17:36,639 --> 00:17:38,506
- OH...OH...

344
00:17:38,539 --> 00:17:40,039
- MMM.
MOMMY...

345
00:17:40,072 --> 00:17:44,439
MAYU...SHE'S HIDING FROM YOU
IN THE CLOSET.

346
00:17:44,472 --> 00:17:48,472
- HUH?
- HURRY AND GET HER, MOMMY.

347
00:17:53,339 --> 00:17:57,772
- I'M AT MY HOUSE.
THIS IS HOW I DIED.

348
00:17:59,172 --> 00:18:02,406
NOBODY SAVED ME
BECAUSE THEY DIDN'T
KNOW I WAS HERE.

349
00:18:02,439 --> 00:18:05,972
- MAYU!
MAYU, WHERE ARE YOU?

350
00:18:06,006 --> 00:18:07,072
- IS THAT YOU, MOMMY?

351
00:18:07,106 --> 00:18:10,206
- WHERE ARE YOU?
ANSWER ME!

352
00:18:11,239 --> 00:18:13,772
THERE YOU ARE!

353
00:18:13,806 --> 00:18:15,906
COME ON, MAYU.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE!

354
00:18:15,939 --> 00:18:18,572
- HOW MANY TIMES
DO I HAVE TO TELL YOU?

355
00:18:18,606 --> 00:18:22,372
I'M DEAD, YOU STUPID IDIOT!
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

356
00:18:22,406 --> 00:18:25,506
WHY DON'T YOU--AAH!
AAH!

357
00:18:26,339 --> 00:18:27,406
- [BOTH SCREAMING]

358
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:29,772
- [WHINING]

359
00:18:29,806 --> 00:18:30,906
- MAYU!

360
00:18:30,939 --> 00:18:33,606
- [BOTH GRUNTING]

361
00:18:38,606 --> 00:18:40,006
- DON'T LET GO!

362
00:18:40,039 --> 00:18:42,639
- [WHIMPERING]

363
00:18:47,172 --> 00:18:48,572
- YOU HAVE TO GO HOME!

364
00:18:48,606 --> 00:18:51,739
GO HOME AND MAKE UP
WITH YOUR MOTHER!

365
00:18:58,439 --> 00:19:03,239
YOUR MOTHER LOVES YOU NOW,
AND SHE ALWAYS DID LOVE YOU!

366
00:19:04,339 --> 00:19:09,872
DON'T YOU WANT TO MAKE UP
WITH HER BEFORE YOU SAY
GOOD-BYE FOR GOOD?

367
00:19:14,706 --> 00:19:18,972
- ISN'T MOMMY MAD AT ME?
- HUH?

368
00:19:19,006 --> 00:19:23,806
- ARE YOU SURE
MOMMY'S NOT MAD?

369
00:19:23,839 --> 00:19:26,039
- SHE'S NOT MAD, REALLY.

370
00:19:26,072 --> 00:19:29,339
SHE JUST LOVES YOU
AND MISSES YOU, THAT'S ALL.

371
00:19:29,372 --> 00:19:31,972
- [WHIMPERING]

372
00:19:34,772 --> 00:19:38,172
- MAYU, YOU KNOW YOUR MOM
BETTER THAN ANYONE.

373
00:19:38,206 --> 00:19:41,006
SHE'D NEVER BE MAD AT YOU.

374
00:19:47,372 --> 00:19:49,939
- MOMMY!

375
00:19:49,972 --> 00:19:53,272
I MISS YOU, MOMMY!
I WANT TO SAY SORRY TO YOU!

376
00:19:53,306 --> 00:19:55,872
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED
TO MAKE UP WITH YOU!

377
00:19:55,906 --> 00:19:58,572
I'M SORRY, MOMMY!

378
00:20:25,172 --> 00:20:27,672
- MAYU?

379
00:20:32,739 --> 00:20:35,406
- MOMMY?
- HUH?

380
00:20:36,039 --> 00:20:37,939
MAYU?

381
00:20:37,972 --> 00:20:43,072
- I'M SORRY, MOMMY.
WILL YOU FORGIVE ME?

382
00:20:44,372 --> 00:20:46,939
- YES.

383
00:20:46,972 --> 00:20:48,206
- HMM.

384
00:20:48,239 --> 00:20:52,172
BYE, MOMMY.
I HAVE TO GO NOW.

385
00:20:56,072 --> 00:20:58,039
- [SIGHS]

386
00:20:58,072 --> 00:21:00,672
- I HOPE MAYU'S ALL RIGHT NOW.

387
00:21:00,706 --> 00:21:03,406
- WHAT WERE YOU THINKING,
GOING IN THERE ALL ALONE?

388
00:21:03,439 --> 00:21:06,339
THAT GIRL COULD HAVE EASILY
PULLED YOU INTO HELL, KAGOME,

389
00:21:06,372 --> 00:21:09,572
AND I WOULDN'T HAVE
BEEN ABLE TO SAVE YOU.

390
00:21:10,572 --> 00:21:13,339
- IT WAS WORTH THE RISK.

391
00:21:14,339 --> 00:21:18,306
ONE WEEK LATER, SATORU CAME HOME
FROM THE HOSPITAL.

392
00:21:20,439 --> 00:21:23,139
- KAGOME?
- HUH?

393
00:21:25,072 --> 00:21:26,072
IT'S YOU!

394
00:21:26,106 --> 00:21:28,072
- I WANTED TO SEE YOU
ONE LAST TIME BEFORE I LEFT.

395
00:21:28,106 --> 00:21:31,572
- I LOVE YOUR SUMMER KIMONO.
YOU LOOK ADORABLE!

396
00:21:31,606 --> 00:21:34,706
- THANKS!
MY MOMMY MADE IT JUST FOR ME.

397
00:21:34,739 --> 00:21:37,672
I'D BETTER BE GOING NOW.
BYE!

398
00:21:37,706 --> 00:21:40,139
[FLUTE PLAYING]

399
00:21:42,139 --> 00:21:46,072
- MAYU, I DON'T THINK YOU WERE
EVER AN EVIL SPIRIT.

400
00:21:46,106 --> 00:21:48,139
YOU WERE JUST
AN ORDINARY LITTLE GIRL

401
00:21:48,172 --> 00:21:51,772
WHO LOVED HER MOM
MORE THAN ANYTHING.

402
00:21:52,639 --> 00:21:55,206
- [LAUGHING]

403
00:22:08,881 --> 00:22:11,648
- [SINGING IN JAPANESE]

404
00:23:37,085 --> 00:23:39,385
- INUYASHA IS HALF-DEMON
AND HALF-HUMAN,

405
00:23:39,418 --> 00:23:41,285
AND HIS GOAL IS
TO GATHER THE SHARDS

406
00:23:41,318 --> 00:23:42,518
OF THE SACRED
SHIKON JEWEL

407
00:23:42,552 --> 00:23:44,452
SO HE CAN BECOME
A FULL-FLEDGED DEMON.

408
00:23:44,485 --> 00:23:46,452
DURING OUR SEARCH
FOR THE JEWEL FRAGMENTS,

409
00:23:46,485 --> 00:23:50,218
WE COME TO THE RESCUE OF A GIRL
WHO TAKES US TO AN OLD TEMPLE.

410
00:23:50,252 --> 00:23:53,085
THERE, THE SPIDER LORD
LURKS IN THE SHADOWS.

411
00:23:53,118 --> 00:23:56,652
INUYASHA'S DARK SECRET
IS ABOUT TO BE REVEALED

412
00:23:56,685 --> 00:23:58,785
ON THIS MOONLESS NIGHT.

413
00:23:58,818 --> 00:23:59,485
NEXT TIME,

414
00:23:59,518 --> 00:24:00,852
"THE MYSTERY OF THE NEW MOON

415
00:24:00,885 --> 00:24:02,818
AND THE BLACK-HAIRED INUYASHA."

416
00:24:02,852 --> 00:24:03,852
SEE YOU SOON!

